text: Sandom Branch is a long tributary to Blackbird Creek in New Castle County, Delaware. Sandom Branch is one of the major tributaries to Blackbird Creek above tidal influence. ==Course== Sandom Branch rises on the Duck Creek divide about 2 miles south of Blackbird, Delaware. ==Watershed== Sandom Branch drains of area, receives about 43.8 in/year of precipitation, has a topographic wetness index of 556.57 and is about 22.6% forested. ==See also== *List of Delaware rivers ==Maps== Course and Watershed of Sandom Branch (Blackbird Creek tributary) ==References== Category:Rivers of Delaware Category:Rivers of New Castle County, Delaware
